      'cmgb3qquo000fro80wm3pgakw', 'The United States will remember this day in which it was singled out for attack in the General Assembly for the very act of exercising our right as a sovereign nation. We will remember it when we are called upon to once again make the world''s largest contribution to the United Nations. And we will remember it when so many countries come calling on us, as they so often do, to pay even more and to use our influence for their benefit.', 'During her tenure as UN Ambassador, Haley made this statement at the UN General Assembly after 128 countries voted to condemn the U.S. decision to recognize Jerusalem as Israel''s capital and move the U.S. embassy there. The vote was on a resolution rejecting President Trump''s recognition of Jerusalem as Israel''s capital. Haley had previously threatened consequences for countries that voted against the U.S. position.', 'ORIGINAL', '2017-12-21T00:00:00.000Z',
