      'cmgb84mlm000froa8mbur007h', 'I call on the Palestinian people to elect new leaders, leaders not compromised by terror. I call upon them to build a practicing democracy, based on tolerance and liberty. If the Palestinian people actively pursue these goals, America and the world will actively support their efforts.', 'President Bush delivered a major policy speech in the Rose Garden outlining his vision for Middle East peace. This was the first time a U.S. president explicitly called for Palestinian statehood while simultaneously demanding new Palestinian leadership and an end to terrorism. The speech came during the Second Intifada and following numerous suicide bombings against Israeli civilians.', 'ORIGINAL', '2002-06-23T23:00:00.000Z',
